import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['job_count'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of job count over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Job Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['sex'] = data['sex'].astype('category')
    data = data.groupby(['sex'])['job_count'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['sex'], data['job_count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count by sex?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.bar(data['job'], data['count'])

    plt.xlabel('Job')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
